NOTE: ASSUMPTIONS USED IN PREPARING PROSPECTIVE FINANCIAL INFORMATION
I.	Land cost, development/ construction cost, on-site expenditure, payment of taxes, fees, charges, premiums, interest etc. to any statutory authority and interest payable on amounts borrowed for the project are best-estimates by the management considering the prevailing market rates, applicable laws, amount to be borrowed and the area to be constructed.
II.	Administrative costs and other costs which do not form part of Chartered Accountants Certificate in Form-3 are best-estimates by the management relying on their experience of undertaking real estate projects of similar size and the rates of direct taxes currently applicable to the firm.
III.	The information in respect of sales realization is based on hypothetical assumptions by the management relying on their experience of undertaking real estate projects of similar size in nearby areas and their understanding of prevailing markets situation.
IV.	The information in respect of capital introduced, project loan obtained and other borrowings is estimated by the management on the basis of their estimation of project costs, time schedule of project completion and assumptions of sales realization in respect of the underlying real estate project.
V.	The interest cost is estimated considering the simple average of opening and closing estimated borrowings for each rolling quarter at effective interest rate of Repo rate by the management.
